<Author>xeno111
<Content>Solid stay, centrally located Spent a week here with few complaints. Friendly, effective staff, and, like most Berliners, fluent in English. Breakfast buffet was big with lots of choices. It has the feel of a hotel for business travelers, by which I mean clean, well appointed, but also lacking in character, more of a chain hotel feel. That also means that some service prices are geared to folks on expense accounts. But you can avoid hefty charges for in-room wi-fi by using the free wireless in the lobby. And there's a friendly and much more reasonably priced dry cleaner just a couple of doors down. (Knowledge of a bit of German and/or ability to creatively pantomime helpful there.)It's in a touristy area, which is good and bad. You're close to many major sights, but far from real Berliners. Fortunately a stop for the excellent public transit system is just a block away. Easy to explore the rest of the city. 
