<Author>UCSD
<Content>Pleasant stay at the Relexa in Berlin. We stayed one week at this hotel in late September. As others have mentioned it is on a street with numerous other hotels. We had no issues with street noise, as we asked for a quiet, non-smoking room. The hotel provided us with a room that overlooked a park shared by a number of apartment buildings. The room was quiet, clean and meet our expectations. The hotel primarely caters to European business people and Eurpean tourists. While I speak German, my wife does not, but she had no problem speaking with the staff in english. They were very helpful in answering our questions. The loaction is excellent, as all of the major sites in the Mitte section of Berlin are either within walking distance or a short S-Bahn train ride away. I would recommend this hotel for its location, clean rooms and helpful staff. 
