<Author>USA808
<Content>Nice Treat for the Budget Traveler We paid 82 Euro a night for a Superior room, which is reasonable in comparison to the other lower-quality chain hotels on the same block. The location was perfect, and we walked to many of the tourist sights. Also, the S-Bahn is just steps away. Down the block, you will also find a very reasonably priced grocery store and a cheap internet cafe. The room was very clean, somewhat spacious, and our window overlooked a courtyard below. The bathroom was very classy. We made use of the free sauna facilities in the basement, although this relaxation area is just mediocre. This was the most upscale of hotels on our budget traveler's journey! We did not pay extra for the hotel breakfast (we just bought groceries at the store nearby), and my only complaint is that the receptionist ran my charge card through in dollars, rather than Euros, insisting that this was the cheapest way to go. She didn't give me the choice (I would have chose the local currency), and was somewhat rude when I protested the method of charge. Otherwise, however, this was a good hotel for the price. 
