<Content>Definately not a 4 star I had a great weekend in Berlin (apart from choosing this hotel), I was there for the Anniversary of 50 years of the EU so loads going on. I would definately go back but not to this hotel. Don't get me wrong the location was great, close to Check Point Charlie and to all Public Transport. The only problem was the hotel, firstly this is rated as a 4 star hotel and there is no way this is a 4 star hotel and just to note we certainly paid 4 star prices. The Bedrooms are unbelievably small, we actually asked to be moved but there were no rooms available due to a conference being held that weekend. Our bedroom was at the front of the hotel and the noise from the busy road all through the night was terrrible. It also states that they have a gym, there are only 4 excercise machines here, it like the bedrooms is far too small. Most of the staff OK but there was one in particular when we were checking out that was just so rude. Breakfast is just OK, the continental style. There are alot more hotels to choose from and I would not recommend this one, simply because it is far too overpriced for what you get. 
