<Author>jetsetter1982
<Content>Good location but not recommended for an extended stay My girlfriend and I are just back from a week in Berlin staying at the Relexa hotel. We booked a superior room for an extra 拢30 over the week. As a previous reviewer commented this is a worthwhile investment as the size of the room we got was only a typical size for a standard British room and I could imagine the standard room option in the Relexa may be quite cramped. The room was equipped with a lovely bathroom, a personal safe and a minibar which is what you expect from a four star hotel.The location of the hotel was excellent for the S-Bahn, with a station less than five minutes walk away. The hotel also has a supermarket and local sites including Checkpoint Charlie five minutes away. The street the hotel is on contains four hotels side by side, resulting in the road being quite noisy at night. With the lack of a/c in the room we kept the window open most of the night which disrupted our sleep on occasion.Breakfast at the hotel was included in the price which is a big bonus when you stay for the week. However with coach parties arriving virtually every night at the hotel, the standard continental breakfast was always busy no matter what time we came down. The hotel does not seem to have the facilities to cope with a semi-busy hotel. It was clearly under staffed, with you feeling under pressure to leave your table quickly to allow someone else to eat. Our last breakfast in the hotel encapsulates the issue when we had to share a table of four with two other tourists! Overall it is a standard four star hotel in a good location for Berlin's attractions which would suit a two/three night stay. However with the lack of a/c in the room, poor breakfast facilities and most of the staff only understanding basic english I would hold back in recommending the hotel to anyone planning an extended stay in Berlin. 
