<Author>ovelho
<Content>Both Very Cool and Too Warm A very nice place, helpful staff, good location, but wasn't quite all we hoped. We wanted a twin room which apparently they don't have so we had only one queen bed---crowded for two big people. The weather was very hot, and the rooms have no air conditioning or fans. We thought such a modern **** hotel would have AC, even though many hotels in Germany do not. The big window/door did open widely to the courtyard, which helped, but there wasn't much breese most of the time. The location is close to the S Bahn, but that's a separate system from the U Bahn, so it was usually helpful only to get to Potsdamer Platz where we walked to the U Bahn station. Breakfast was very good and INCLUDED, which it wasn't at other hotels we reserved via Expedia, Hotels, etc.(where it cost 15-18 euros EACH) The hotel was generally very clean and well decorated, EXCEPT....the rooms have yellow carpeting which shows every little spill and stain, and there were lots of them. It gave an otherwise spotless room an unpleasant impression. Berlin's a great city---very modern and very historic, with people from all over the world! 
